flowRoot.flowPara: 1. Main menu : user chooses which of two activities to undertake. In this mockup, the user clicks "Sign a key"

2. Camera off screen : video devices are enumerated in a drop-down menu at the top of the screen. In the centre, a pictogram depicting a Monkeycode appears where in place of the video stream. To proceed, the user must turn on the camera.

text.tspan: When you're ready to scan the person's Monkeycode, turn on the camera using the button below.

flowRoot.flowPara: 3. Camera on screen : a video stream appears in place of the pictogram. The user is instructed to show the Monkeycode to the camera. The camera can be turned off at any time.

text.tspan: Place the person's Monkeycode in front of the camera.

flowRoot.flowPara: 4. Monkeycode frame and key search : the video stream is replaced with the still frame in which the Monkeycode was detected, with a red square around the detected code. Monkeysign automatically searches the user's keyring, the local network and the Internet for the public key matching the Monkeycode.

6b. Key not found! : the OpenPGP public key couldn't be found anywhere, so Monkeysign can't proceed right now. The user can click Previous to return to screen 2, or Cancel to return to the main menu or enter a name describing the name of the person's Monkeycode and save those together.

6a. Signing options : the user is offered several options of what to do with the signature. (Exclusive or not?) The signature is created and acted upon when the "Sign the key" button is pressed. Previous returns the user to screen 2. Cancel returns to main menu.
8a. Success dialog : user is happy, clicks finish to go back to main menu

text.tspan: Monkeysign sucessfully completed the selected key signing operation.
Save it locally to a file

flowRoot.flowPara: 8b. Error dialog : show the operation that failed including some debugging information. The user can click Previous to go back to the key signing options (screen 6a) or Cancel to go back to the main menu.

Sorry, we couldn't find the key matching this Monkeycode.
The key was found. Which user ids do you want to sign?

flowRoot.flowPara: 6c. It's you! : the OpenPGP fingerprint scanned matches a key which the user controls.
